The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Thursday, May 27, 2004 				 Veerappan gunrunner caught 
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 																								Chennai, May 26: A close associate of Veerappan, Suba Elavarasan, was arrested by the special task force of Tamil Nadu police around Tuesday midnight.																								Elavarasan, who heads the banned Tamil extremist outfit Tamilar Viduthalai Iyakkam (Tamils Liberation Movement), had supplied an AK-47 rifle to the sandalwood smugglers gang.																								A special task force team intercepted Elavarasan and his associate Sagadevan at the confluence of the Palar and Cauvery rivers, additional director-general of police Vijayakumar said today. He heads the force in the state. Earlier, director-general of police I.K.Govind announced the arrests, saying that with Elavarasan behind bars, we can get the prize catch Veerappan.																								Govind made the announcement after a function at the residence of the British deputy high commissioner Stuart Innes.																								In 2001, Elavarasan had supplied an AK-47 to Veerappans gang through Arivazhagan, a member of his outfit. He had also sent four of his cadres to help Veerappan kidnap former Karnataka minister H. Nagappa in 2002. 
